rComments: Amazing and thoughtful professor. Really knows what she is talking about and uses great references to historical times to make the course easier to understand. Highly recommend.

Love her! She is so excited to teach! She's teaching my theories of crime class at Laurier right now and her class is probably my favorite this semester! Super kind and helpful during office hours and she actually cares if you do well in her class!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: She enjoys hearing her own voice and is belittling to others.

I definitely wouldn't take this class again. This professor goes overboard with lectures. Seems as though you're bothering her when asking for any feedback, or even a simple question in regards to grades and when they'll be posted.

Very easy to take notes in her lectures. She really puts an emphasis on the points in the slide before discussing it so you don't get lost. Nice & chipper. Haven't had exams yet but so far she's given full marks on weekly activities - I think if you are careful to follow her guidelines you will have no problem.
Amzing teacher, super interesting lectures. Tough grader though so study up!
Class was partially enjoyable until the exam where it was the most confusing thing I have ever read and the best part was we had 8% of the final mark based on a 40 minute movie!

Will not prepare you for final exam,  tells you it's cumulative but really only asks questions on two chapters.  Grades unfairly and all together will screw you over in the end.  Would not take again.  Her lectures put me to sleep.

Very  sweet prof, open to conversation, tries to make activities fun, if it weren't for being Fridays at 8:30am, the class would be amazing. Lectures tend to be lengthy, always an activity that for the most part you have to go to class to get full marks for. Loves to use twitter for discussion.

Her classes were very boring. Her essay marks were poor and many A students got a poor mark.   She devoted an entire three-hour lecture to how to write an essay, despite all students having already taken a course in essay writing.   She conducted her classes by simply reading from a paper then a ten minute discussion at the end of class.

Im a Carleton Alum from 2012 and upon reading this I don't understand the negative feedback. Negative comments is usually individuals  who shot themselves in the foot. Every time I approached her, she was easy going and fair. Definitely enjoyed the lectures and the encouraged participation, and, would definitely take one of her classes again.
can be a hard marker but i don't get all the negative reviews.... she was nice and helpful every time i talked to her.

Warning: she is a horrible professor. One of the worst classes I have taken to date. If you are taking Criminology, avoid taking this course with her, she is extremely unhelpful, cold, and does not apply Law to this course even though it's a LAWS course.

One of my worst profs to date. She says she's willing to help but in reality she is not unless you want rude comments back. The course is a sociology course, not a law course like it is indicated.  She is not knowledgeable about law and tells you should've taken another course if that was what you wanted to discuss. A real shame of a class. Avoid!

Extremely disappointed. She is rude and unapproachable. Does not have a welcoming environment. Her assignments are unclear and marked very hardly. She is not knowledgeable about law and focuses on sociological concepts even though it is a law course.  I do not recommend her at all. Her feedback is not helpful either, it's rather rude.

she seems friendly but teaching is not her forte. She is unclear, unhelpful, and rude. She wants you to participate in class but doesn't provide a comforting environment. She does not provide constructive criticism and marks extremely unfairly without proper reasonings. I do not recommend her as a prof and I regret taking this course.

An uninteresting and useless class. It is a law course but is based on a Sociological approach. The professor is not helpful at all and her assignments are very vague and instructions are unclear. The fact that she gives a take home midterm during reading week is added to her list of negatives. Don't take this class!!

An absolutely phenomenal professor, can't say enough good things. Always willing to help her students and always had fun teaching the class and really made an effort to make the theory heavy lectures enjoyable. The exams however are tough as they are open book but as long as you keep up with the readings you should be fine. Once again Great Prof!!

Prof Dej was a great teacher. Her essays and tests were sometimes unclear of what she expected but once you went and saw her she was very good at clarifying anything. I would definitely recommend her to anyone!
Hard marker - very picky. Conveyed the subject material well but gives too many essays
